          "date": "2012-10-23 08:05:06.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2079 llog: dump attributes in error case",
        "message": "LU-2079 llog: dump attributes in error case\n\nthis is a strange situation when non-zero size is returned\non an empty llog. the patch should dump attributes so we\ncan check what's wrong. at the moment the idea is that for\na reason llog was created with the wrong type of directory\n(supposed to be a regular file) and for directories we do\nnot return size stored in zfs as it's equal number of names,\ninstead we calculate it as number of blocks multiplied by\nblocksize.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2238f3f7f57a1f190d82450ab4db3916c7b93676\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
